<h3><font color="#408080"><a name="information">General Information</a></font></h3>

<p>If you cannot pay the full amount of income tax you owe on your New York State income
tax return, you can ask to make monthly installment payments.&nbsp; However, you will be
charged interest and you may be charged a late payment penalty on any tax not paid by its
due date, even if your request to pay in installments is granted.&nbsp; To limit the
interest and any penalty charges, you should file your return by April 15, 1999, and pay as much
of the tax as possible with your return.</p>

<p>To be considered for an installment payment agreement, complete all information
requested on the online Form DTF-383.&nbsp; Your request will be considered based upon the
information you provide.</p>
